bc-vigil (0.4.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * HDD/SSD/removable/network detection on dedup target creation
    via /proc/self/mountinfo and /sys/block/*/queue/rotational.
  * HDD detected -> threads forced to 1 (2-10x speedup reported
    vs multi-threaded reads on spinning rust); an advanced
    override checkbox keeps any user-specified value.
  * Network filesystem detected (NFS, SMB, SSHFS, 9p, ceph, AFS,
    gluster, rclone) -> target creation refused unless an opt-in
    checkbox is ticked, with a prominent warning on degraded
    performance.
  * Target detail page now shows the detected storage backend
    (SSD / HDD / removable / network / unknown) and the block
    device name.
  * Scan locking: trigger_scan raises ScanAlreadyRunningError if
    another PENDING/RUNNING scan exists for the same target.
    The run_scan route redirects silently to the active scan.
    Scheduled cron runs are skipped cleanly in that case.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 19:00:00 +0000

bc-vigil (0.3.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Dedup quarantine feature: select duplicate files in the scan
    detail view and move them to a reversible trash with full
    audit trail instead of deleting them outright.
  * New table DedupDeletion (scan_id, group_id, original_path,
    trash_path, size, hash, stored_mode, status, deleted_at,
    restored_at, purged_at, triggered_by, error).
  * Safety: re-hash with SHA256 at move-time to catch TOCTOU
    races; refuse symlinks / hardlinked-to-survivor / size drift
    / hash mismatch / missing source; minimum one survivor per
    group enforced; bulk threshold with explicit opt-in.
  * Storage: rename() atomic when same filesystem, fallback to
    copy2+fsync+unlink otherwise; warning shown for cross-FS
    items in the preview.
  * Restore button moves the file back to its original location
    (refused if a file now sits there); purge button deletes it
    for good.
  * Retention 7 days by default, configurable via
    BC_VIGIL_DEDUP_TRASH_RETENTION_DAYS; automatic purge job
    (APScheduler interval 24h). BC_VIGIL_DEDUP_TRASH_DIR to
    override the default <data_dir>/dedup/trash/ location (useful
    when duplicates sit on a different filesystem).
  * New /dedup/trash page with status filter and per-item
    restore/purge actions; sidebar entry with badge.
  * admin reset/restore now clear the trash directory when set
    separately from data_dir.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 18:00:00 +0000

bc-vigil (0.2.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * New dedup/ module: parallel duplicate-file finder backed by
    bc-duplicate. Mirrors integrity/: targets, schedules, scans,
    cancel (SIGTERM/SIGKILL), RSS sampling, APScheduler cron jobs,
    retention purge, CSV export of duplicate groups, FR/EN UI,
    sidebar entries "Doublons" and "Analyses doublons".
  * New tables DedupTarget, DedupSchedule, DedupScan, DedupGroup
    (all new columns nullable — _add_missing_columns stays
    compatible for in-place upgrades).
  * New settings: BC_VIGIL_BC_DUPLICATE_BINARY (default
    "bc-duplicate"), data_dir/dedup/ stores JSON reports.
  * admin_ops backup/restore/reset now cover dedup_dir and count
    dedup scans as active.
  * Recommends: bc-duplicate; postinst warns when missing.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 17:00:00 +0000

bc-vigil (0.1.3-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Fix scans permanently failing with "malformed left digest file"
    once an empty target was scanned: 0.1.1 synthesized a summary-only
    digest for empty targets, but bc-hash diff rejects that format,
    which broke every subsequent scheduled scan whose baseline was the
    synth file. run_hash no longer synthesizes; empty scans are stored
    with digest_path=NULL, and a baseline that is empty or unusable is
    automatically replaced by the first real scan (self-heal for prod
    DBs already poisoned by 0.1.1).

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 09:34:35 +0000

bc-vigil (0.1.2-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Fix schedule form silently ignoring the time picked by the user:
    the template rendered two inputs named "time" (one per mode panel
    plus a global hidden fallback at 03:00). Weekly/monthly panels
    only updated the first match via JS, while the hidden one shipped
    with its default value to the server. Each mode panel now owns a
    single visible name="time" input, panels are disabled by JS when
    unused, no hidden fallback, no onchange glue.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sat, 18 Apr 2026 21:00:00 +0000

bc-vigil (0.1.1-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Fix "unexpected: No such file" when scanning an empty target:
    bc-hash exits 0 without producing a digest, run_hash now synthesizes
    an empty-summary digest so the baseline/diff flow stays valid.
  * systemd unit: grant AmbientCapabilities=CAP_DAC_READ_SEARCH so the
    unprivileged bc-vigil user can read /etc/shadow, SSH host keys,
    /etc/ufw/*, etc. Read-only capability, no write privilege added.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sat, 18 Apr 2026 20:30:00 +0000

